external_knowledge:
- Active employees are those whose employment status is 'Active';
- The next review date is calculated by adding 6 months to the date of the most recent review;
- The performance review score is an indicator of the employee's performance during the last review.

sql:
SELECT employee_id, project_name
FROM employee_progress
WHERE completion_percentage > 50;

external_knowledge:
- "Top-performing employee" refers to the employee with the highest total salary who also has the highest average completion percentage of projects;
- "Total salary" is the sum of all new salaries from the salary history;
- "Project completion" is measured by the average completion percentage of projects.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(employee_id) 
FROM employee_trainings 
WHERE participation_status = 'Completed';

external_knowledge:
- "Total salary change" is the sum of all salary increments and decrements for each employee;
- If an employee has no salary changes, their total salary change is 0;
- The results are ordered by the employee's last name and first name.

- 'seasoned professionals' refers to employees who are older than 30 years;
- 'shone brightly in their performance reviews' refers to employees with an average performance score greater than 80;
- 'threshold of excellence' refers to the average performance score of 80.

sql:
SELECT visit_id
FROM office_visits
WHERE visit_duration > 1;

SELECT e.first_name
FROM employees e
WHERE e.salary > (SELECT AVG(salary) FROM employees);

external_knowledge:
- "gardeners" refers to employees;
- "blooming flowers" refers to projects;
- "surpassed the halfway mark" refers to projects with a completion percentage greater than 50%;
- "sections of the garden" refers to departments.
